President Muhammadu Buhari has approved the re-appointment of Abba Kyari as his chief of Staff (COS).  The President has also re-appointed Mr Boss Mustapha as Secretary to the Government of the Federation (SGF). Senior Special Assistant to the President Garba Shehu disclosed this yesterday while briefing State House Correspondents.  Garba had earlier issued a statement in which he said that both appointments take effect from May 29, 2019. According to him, the appointments were parts of efforts to restrategise to move the country forward with the beginning of another four year term of the Buhari administration. President Buhari also announced additional appointments. Most of the appointees are those who worked in the first term.  They include Mohammed Sarki Abba – Senior Special Assistant to the President (Household and Social Events), Ya’u Shehu Darazo – Senior Special Assistant to the President (Special Duties), and Dr Suhayb Sanusi Rafindadi – Personal Physician to the President Others are Ambassador Lawal A. Kazaure – State Chief of Protocol, Sabiu Yusuf – Special Assistant (Office of the President), Saley Yuguda – Special Assistant (House Keeping), Ahmed Muhammed Mayo – Special Assistant (Finance & Administration), Mohammed Hamisu Sani – Special Assistant (Special Duties), Friday Bethel – Personal Assistant (General Duties), Sunday Aghaeze – Personal Assistant (State Photographer) and Bayo Omoboriowo – Personal Assistant (Presidential Photographer).